<p>A fairly well-wrapped first book in a trilogy, that has some very imaginative and well worked through takes on what Martian life may have looked like at the time. I love the imagery, and the theology isn't as worked through everything as the other books. - <a href="https://github.com/RichardLitt">@RichardLitt</a></p>
