<h4><a id="user-content-1984-1949-by-george-orwell-41--" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true" href="#1984-1949-by-george-orwell-41--"><svg class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5470.1984" rel="nofollow">1984</a> (1949) <em>by <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/George_Orwell" rel="nofollow">George Orwell</a></em> [4.1] <g-emoji class="g-emoji" alias="star2" fallback-src="https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f31f.png">ðŸŒŸ</g-emoji> <g-emoji class="g-emoji" alias="fire" fallback-src="https://assets-cdn.github.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f525.png">ðŸ”¥</g-emoji></h4>
<blockquote>
<p>Written in 1948, <em>1984</em> was George Orwellâ€™s chilling prophecy about the future.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>While 1984 has come and gone, Orwellâ€™s narrative is more timely that ever. <em>1984</em> presents a â€œnegative utopia,â€ that is at once a startling and haunting vision of the worldâ€”so powerful that itâ€™s completely convincing from start to finish. No one can deny the power of this novel, its hold on the imaginations of entire generations of readers, or the resiliency of its admonitionsâ€”a legacy that seems to grow, not lessen, with the passage of time.</p>
</blockquote>
